ANS-hold diagnostic status
--------------------------
The DT-property variant reached BusyBox. An over-broad /proc/kmsg filter then
replayed historical PMGR output, so the module result did not drain before the
transport disconnected. The m1n1 proxy remained unresponsive after the
documented kisd restart and explicit DebugUSB re-entry. Live work stopped.

Repeated recovery transport signature
-------------------------------------
A later remote reboot reached a fresh Running proxy, but both permitted proxy
attempts again received zero reply bytes. Both recovery logs are exactly 15044
bytes and end with:

  52 75 6e 6e 69 6e 67 20 70 72 6f 78 79 2e 2e 2e 0a ff 55 aa
  Running proxy........U.

m1n1's REQ_BOOT value is 0x04aa55ff, so its little-endian fourth byte is 0x04
(VEOF). A fresh kisd PTY is canonical on macOS because kisd can only set its
master raw on Linux. The apparent reader drained text but the line discipline
intercepted the binary startup packet. The recovery helper now sets the slave
raw before entering DebugUSB. No additional target attempt followed this
finding.

