Authorized recovery retry
-------------------------
The next fresh reboot produced a complete raw-mode startup reply:

  ff 55 aa 04 00 00 00 00 ... dc 92 9b f4

Both proxy attempts still timed out. Reattaching a reader then drained 3277
bytes of historical Linux #23 ANS-hold output, including the old shell's
`cat /proc/kmsg` command; this was not a new boot. A second reboot stopped at
the end of iBoot Stage2 (11259 bytes stable for 30 seconds) without reaching
m1n1. A final fresh recovery failed at macvdmtool's DebugUSB VDM. kisd was
stopped. The display showed Apple's "macOS on the selected disk needs to be
reinstalled" screen: evidence that iBoot identified the system volume, not
that Linux NVMe ran. No kernel handoff, module load, namespace access, or
storage command occurred during these retries.

ANS-hold set live boot (kernel #24)
-----------------------------------
After the physical power cycle, the hash-verified Image-sart-trace,
t6040-j614s-dcuart-nvme-ans-hold.dtb, and ANS-hold initramfs reached BusyBox.
The staged result was:

  __NVME_CORE_BEGIN__
  core_rc=0
  __NVME_CORE_END__
  __NVME_APPLE_BEGIN__

The target then watchdog-reset and kisd disconnected. This boot had no kmsg
relay, and ttydc is not a printk console. Therefore the missing driver trace
lines do not identify a new earlier boundary; the reset is confirmed but its
last internal checkpoint was not observable. No namespace or storage command
was issued.

Prepared replacement initramfs with an opt-in current-boot `trace:` relay:

  initramfs-dcuart-nvme-ans-hold-trace.cpio.gz
  8942b1bd009cd9fe0adeadea3de60d6f068120ae2b8327e0ae1df2c852f40ea5

Boot it with EXTRA_BOOTARGS=t6040.trace_relay=1 and the unchanged Image/DTB.
